# Keep a Changelog Standards

Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/) + [SemVer](https://semver.org/).

## Change Types

- **Added** — new features, endpoints, config, docs
- **Changed** — existing functionality, non-breaking API changes, perf
- **Deprecated** — features planned for removal
- **Removed** — deleted features, endpoints, dependencies
- **Fixed** — bug fixes, crash fixes, perf issues
- **Security** — vulnerability patches, dependency updates

## Structure

```markdown
## [Unreleased]

### Added
- Multi-language support ([#123](https://github.com/user/repo/pull/123))

### Fixed
- Memory leak in background worker ([#128](https://github.com/user/repo/issues/128))

[Unreleased]: https://github.com/user/repo/compare/v1.2.0...HEAD
[1.2.0]: https://github.com/user/repo/compare/v1.1.0...v1.2.0
```

## Entry Quality

Good — specific, user-facing, with PR/issue link:
`- Race condition in payment processing causing duplicate charges ([#128])`

Bad — vague, no context:
`- Fixed bug`

## Rules

- Update with every PR
- Write from user's perspective
- Include issue/PR numbers
- ISO dates (YYYY-MM-DD)
- Unreleased section at top
- Skip internal-only changes
